Description: TV Guide Meets Discord/Slack - Real Time Chat for Live TV
Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Couchmate provides a real time chat platform for all live TV airings for the United States and Canada, currently. It is available iOS and Android. The platform dynamically creates ephemeral chat rooms for these airings that are created 15 minutes before any given show starts and then boots all users from the room 15 minutes after the show ends. These 15 minute buffer periods are for discussion to warm up and cool down with the show. Users interact in a very similar manner that they would in a Slack or Discord. Chat features like @ing other users, posting gifs and reacting to messages are available. They can also dynamically create what are called "Hashrooms" which are rooms within rooms to narrow discussion during a particular show. These are equitable to Slack or Discord channels. When users first enter the app, they are anonymous. Anonymous users are assigned a random username and have the ability to start chatting right away. Users can register their accounts (via email) to change their username and perform other more privileged actions in the app. Along with being anonymous, they are assigned a generic channel listing grid that corresponds to their current (phone) timezone. This consists of the major networks and other popular, yet non-local, channels. If users register their accounts, they have the ability to enter their zip code and change their TV provider to a local one to gain a larger channel list/local channels. Users (anonymous and registered) have the ability to "follow" series, sports teams or one-off shows via notifications. Notifications are sent out when the rooms open for the given show, to which users can instantly pop right into the show room and start chatting.
Industry Groups: Apps, Internet Services, Media and Entertainment, Mobile, Software, Video

It reduces your ability to see clearly, and makes it nearly impossible to see into the water. Chalant Polarized sunglasses filter out glare and transmit only the light you need, providing you with increased visual clarity while reducing eyestrain. Chalant Sunglasses lenses are unique, because they contain a special filter that blocks this type of intense reflected light, reducing glare. Chalant sunglasses serve two main purposes: First, they effectively block nearly all damaging UV-rays and help to keep your eyes protected from the effects of harsh sunlight. Description: ElixinPharma was founded in 1999 to assist new and emerging pharmaceutical companies with their Chemistry, Manufacturing.
Headquarters Regions: Greater San Diego Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: ElixinPharma was founded in 1999 to assist new and emerging pharmaceutical companies with their Chemistry, Manufacturing and Controls (CMC) needs. Over the years, we have built a reputation for providing high quality, highly strategic management of the complex CMC issues surrounding not only small molecules but also novel technologies such as oligonucleotides. Our client base ranges from small venture-backed start-up companies to large multi-national pharmaceutical companies. Currently, over 90 % of our projects are in the area of oligonucleotide therapeutics, including antisense, aptamers, PEGylated aptamers, DNA duplex decoys, siRNA, and other complex oligonucleotides in a variety of formulations for parenteral, topical, intravitreal, pulmonary and oral delivery. DNAWe are intimately familiar with the challenges faced by start-up companies with respect to meeting development milestones, partnering issues, regulatory interactions and cash flow management. We work with these companies on topics beyond the science, helping to manage the development programs in a staged manner to better utilize limited resources while minimizing overall risk to the program. As larger pharma companies have entered this field through maturation of their internal programs or through licensing agreements with smaller companies, new challenges have emerged; CMC and regulatory teams must adapt their internal systems, usually geared towards small molecule therapeutics, to the unique requirements of oligonucleotides. We work with these teams to leverage their strengths while implementing innovative techniques to effectively manage the new programs.

Description: The Pearl by Nexnet is a method that allows viewers to respond to an on-screen cue (a Pearl icon appears) with their remote control,
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: The Pearl by Nexnet is a method that allows viewers to respond to an on-screen cue (a "Pearl" icon appears) with their remote control, resulting in an instantaneous e-mail to the individuals personal e-mail in-box regarding the topic or product appearing on the screen at that time. The topic can be informational or promotional and also works with recorded content.  This e-mail generated from the click of the remote guides the viewer effortlessly to the exact information or product requested. Visits to these websites can be tracked — a significant interest to advertisers. The links can be sent to any number of e-mail addresses in the household.  Nexnet provides all e-mail creation, customization and reporting through its web interface with the Nexnet server database for PEARL. Advertisers, Content Providers and Operators can facilitate all their PEARL needs through an on-line system that can be accessed from anywhere around the world giving maximum flexibility to campaign creation and management.  Nexnet provides a deeper level of detail about the subscriber base.  Data is accumulated based on the viewer instead of the household. This helps the operator understand who watches TV in each household, which TV/STB they are using and what the viewer is interested in watching. This depth of granularity down to the specific viewer is not available through any other service.
Industry Groups: Advertising, Mobile, Sales and Marketing, Software

Description: SaaS to Support Your Career and Compensation
Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: At Earner, our mission is to right the imbalance of power between professionals and the businesses they work for.  Fundamentally, we believe too many people aren't being paid what they're worth.  It happens for a lot of reasons, but we believe with verified data and and the right support, we can get you the compensation you deserve. Earner helps you get paid fairly. First, we provide a free OfferScore, which is an evaluation of your offer letter (or letters) so you know how the offer measures up.  Most people focus on base and bonus when they look at their offers, but these only make up 70% of your total compensation. We thoroughly assess your PTO policies, 401K retirement plans, health benefits, commuter stipends, and many more to find the true value of your offer.  We build our free OfferScore by comparing your offers to thousands of others from companies like Google, Amazon, Microsoft, Facebook, Oracle, and privately-held startups - then use that data to help you negotiate effectively for a better compensation package. With an OfferScore in hand, we then work with you to build a Gameplan - that's what we call our partnering approach to negotiation.  For a flat fee, we work with you throughout the negotiation process to help you get what you deserve.  The Gameplan lays out an overall approach and specific guidance for every aspect of your negotiation, including likely counter-arguments.  We update the Gameplan as we work with you, so you always have our best advice and the right language to make your case.  If our work together doesn't result in an improved offer, you pay nothing - that's our commitment to seeing you succeed. Earner's mission is to make every professional feel valued and fulfilled by their work, and that can't happen if you're not being paid fairly.  Join us, work with us, support us in this goal!
